1
00:01:01,039 --> 00:01:01,640
Guards!

2
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:02,000
Yes, my lord.

3
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:02,799
Yes, my lord.

4
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,560
Tie him up!

5
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,159
Yes!

6
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:06,959
Yes!

7
00:01:08,599 --> 00:01:09,400
Hmph.

8
00:01:16,959 --> 00:01:17,760
Qi Zhi.

9
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:21,640
I'm sorry,

10
00:01:24,239 --> 00:01:25,000
Yun'er.

11
00:01:25,799 --> 00:01:26,760
Congratulations,

12
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,879
Prince Rong.

13
00:01:39,879 --> 00:01:40,599
Men of Rong City

14
00:01:40,599 --> 00:01:42,040
must remain faithful for life.

15
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,200
Unless divorced, men can't have affairs,

16
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,439
and certainly cannot remarry.

17
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,640
Otherwise, it's a betrayal of one's wife,

18
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,840
the crime of bigamy,

19
00:01:51,799 --> 00:01:52,959
punishable by beheading.

20
00:01:58,079 --> 00:01:59,439
What exactly are you trying to do?

21
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,760
You never divorced me,

22
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,480
yet I married Yun'er.

23
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,159
I've already broken the law.

24
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,200
So either divorce me now,

25
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,639
or kill me.

26
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:10,840
Enough!

27
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,240
Take him away.

28
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,039
Wait.

29
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:15,560
Even royalty must answer to the law.

30
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,080
If you bend the law for personal reasons,

31
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,039
how will you command respect?

32
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:22,319
You really think I wouldn't dare kill you?

33
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:27,080
I've never thought that for a moment.

34
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,639
Do you despise me that much?

35
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:31,960
Hate me so deeply?

36
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,800
No.

37
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,280
I'm not the one who hates you.

38
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:45,919
My husband and I

39
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:47,280
were childhood sweethearts,

40
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,439
deeply in love.

41
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,599
I wanted to spend my whole life with him.

42
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,280
But you kept forcing me to marry others,

43
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,039
driving him into a deep depression,

44
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,039
bedridden, never to recover.

45
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,479
And my brother,

46
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,000
forced into concubinage despite his love,

47
00:03:02,639 --> 00:03:03,800
miserable day after day,

48
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,680
attempting to end his life many times.

49
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,439
All of this is your doing.

50
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,159
Tell me, shouldn't I hate you?

51
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:14,800
Then go on, do it!

52
00:03:17,439 --> 00:03:19,159
So what if you hate me?

53
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,800
So what if you've captured me?

54
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,000
Inside this manor,

55
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:27,039
there are three hundred guards.

56
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:27,759
Outside the city,

57
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:29,479
five thousand elite soldiers.

58
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:31,800
Do you really think

59
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:35,000
you can escape Rong City?

60
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,360
Don't be so sure.

61
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,639
Qi Zhi!

62
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:40,800
Qi Zhi!

63
00:03:43,479 --> 00:03:44,280
I'm here.

64
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:45,439
Bandeng!

65
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:48,240
You don't have a single person left now.

66
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,240
How could this happen?

67
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:53,840
What did you do?

68
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,240
We did our part.

69
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,240
The rest is up to fate.

70
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,479
I never imagined

71
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:19,600
I'd end up forsaken by everyone.

72
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,560
Bandeng.

73
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:23,800
I...

74
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,439
I'm just a stray dog now.

75
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,199
Don't humiliate me further, my lord.

76
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:30,240
Bandeng,

77
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:32,079
That's not my intention.

78
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,560
I just want you to know

79
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,800
that you were wrong.

80
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,759
Your methods have always been extreme.

81
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,800
You'd stir public outrage sooner or later.

82
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:42,199
So what?

83
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,279
My lord, how could you...

84
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:43,439
Hey.

85
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,639
It's a family matter.

86
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,360
Bandeng,

87
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:52,879
I know you grew up watching men oppress your mother,

88
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,800
and resentment grew within you.

89
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:00,000
Men oppressing women is certainly wrong,

90
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:03,000
but the way you've become now,

91
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,000
how are you unlike the men who killed her?

92
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:09,439
I hope after I leave Rong City,

93
00:05:11,639 --> 00:05:13,240
you'll govern it well

94
00:05:16,199 --> 00:05:16,800
to make up, in some way,

95
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:20,000
for our mistakes.

96
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:23,839
At the end of the day,

97
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:26,560
isn't this all just for a divorce letter?

98
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:28,839
Did it take a mutiny to wake you up?

99
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,279
Why did I do this?

100
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:35,360
Because by rebelling,

101
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,360
at least I could keep you safe.

102
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:55,439
It's the last thing

103
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,560
I can do for you.

104
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,360
Since you no longer love me,

105
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:17,639
just let me go.

106
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,759
Divorce me,

107
00:06:19,759 --> 00:06:23,199
and you can return to your old life.

108
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:27,399
I'll leave this place forever.

109
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,040
Everything between us

110
00:06:33,399 --> 00:06:34,560
was just like a dream.

111
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,160
The hatred,

112
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,480
the love,

113
00:06:43,279 --> 00:06:44,199
let it all be forgotten.

114
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:51,160
It's not that I don't love you.

115
00:06:55,399 --> 00:06:56,240
What did you say?

116
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,879
I just forgot that I love you.

117
00:07:07,279 --> 00:07:08,639
I know I was wrong.

118
00:07:12,839 --> 00:07:14,399
Could you please not leave?

119
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:20,160
I don't want you to go.

120
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:27,000
Please don't go.

121
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,600
Your great kindness

122
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:41,160
will never be forgotten.

123
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,560
If you really want to repay us,

124
00:07:43,759 --> 00:07:45,279
come back to the palace and be emperor!

125
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:46,240
Hey!

126
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:49,199
I object!

127
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:52,639
Everyone,

128
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,680
this one matter alone,

129
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,240
I'm afraid I must...

130
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:01,560
Hey!

131
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,480
Don't listen to her nonsense.

132
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:06,800
Prince Rong and his wife reuniting,

133
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,839
that's what's truly fortunate.

134
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,399
As for

135
00:08:08,399 --> 00:08:09,839
the trivial matter of finding an emperor,

136
00:08:09,839 --> 00:08:10,759
just leave it to me.

137
00:08:10,759 --> 00:08:11,800
You two needn't worry.

138
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:12,839
I'll take my leave now.

139
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,800
Crown Prince, you really won't take the throne?

140
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,399
Forget the throne.

141
00:08:19,639 --> 00:08:21,240
I'd rather go with them to find the next heir.

142
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:23,879
Oh.

143
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:24,639
By the way,

144
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,079
I really like Rong City's new slogan,

145
00:08:27,279 --> 00:08:28,879
"Gender equality," right?

146
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,279
Hey.

147
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:32,440
You see,

148
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,759
even the most domineering woman

149
00:08:35,759 --> 00:08:37,000
has a gentle side after all.

150
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,279
Never seen that side of you.

151
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,919
Who said I don't have one?

152
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,240
I do!

153
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,840
You just can't see it.

154
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,679
Qi Zhi, wait for me!

155
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,600
No way, not waiting.

156
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,279
Don't know you.

157
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:46,080
Hey!

158
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:47,399
Look at him!

159
00:08:59,240 --> 00:08:59,919
Qi Zhi!

160
00:08:59,919 --> 00:09:00,639
Have some water.

161
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:02,440
Sir.

162
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,559
Let me refill your water.

163
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,080
I know

164
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,120
Hua Hua's death

165
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,200
was my fault.

166
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,039
But you're my only friend.

167
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,879
If you ignore me,

168
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,759
I won't have a single friend left.

169
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:23,960
Disgusting.

170
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,200
Hey.

171
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,039
How about my next comic

172
00:09:29,039 --> 00:09:31,399
features you as the main character?

173
00:09:31,679 --> 00:09:33,200
I'll draw your journey to find the heir.

174
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:35,279
It'll definitely be a hit.

175
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,559
Who cares.

176
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,039
Looks like I'll have to use my trump card.

177
00:09:47,639 --> 00:09:49,159
General Li found this.

178
00:09:49,559 --> 00:09:50,799
An egg laid by Hua Hua.

179
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,039
I'm leaving it for you.

180
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,840
We're having a moment, don't ruin it.

181
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,799
Your Highness,

182
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:09,759
Whether inside the palace or out,

183
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,200
you always love running off.

184
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,799
How did you find me?

185
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:15,200
We've caught you over a hundred times.

186
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,399
We're experienced by now.

187
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:18,799
I'm not going back.

188
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,919
I want to go with them

189
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:21,639
to find the heir to the throne.

190
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:24,000
We're not actually here to catch you this time.

191
00:10:24,639 --> 00:10:26,200
General Li sent a message for you.

192
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,399
Over 200,000 Watanabe troops at the border.

193
00:10:29,159 --> 00:10:30,240
They plan to invade Da Liang.

194
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,480
We have 500,000 elite soldiers.

195
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,639
Send them to fight!

196
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:34,679
Sigh.

197
00:10:34,679 --> 00:10:36,080
The south is currently at war.

198
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,840
All our troops have been deployed there.

199
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,200
There's no time to recall them.

200
00:10:39,759 --> 00:10:40,559
Our only option now

201
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:42,600
is to go beg someone for help.

202
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:43,399
Who?

203
00:10:43,639 --> 00:10:44,440
Royal Uncle Liu.

204
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:46,840
He was a fierce warrior in his youth,

205
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,960
and still commands 150,000 troops.

206
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,240
His location

207
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,840
is perfect to intercept them in time.

208
00:10:52,559 --> 00:10:53,399
But...

209
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,000
Hmm?

210
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,080
But what?

211
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:56,799
But when Royal Uncle Liu was young,

212
00:10:57,039 --> 00:10:58,399
he fought my father for the throne,

213
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,840
and things got very ugly.

214
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:02,080
So he fled to a remote northern city

215
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,960
and declared it independent from Da Liang.

216
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,000
This favor,

217
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,240
who knows if he'll even agree to help.

218
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:10,759
That's why we ask you to plead with him,

219
00:11:11,039 --> 00:11:12,399
to see if there's any chance.

220
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:14,440
Such a difficult task,

221
00:11:14,559 --> 00:11:15,639
why does it have to be me?

222
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,480
Envoy Qi and Princess Ouyang are capable.

223
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:22,039
We hope you can lend him a hand.

224
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,039
Hey, chicken farmer,

225
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,840
Will you help us out?

226
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:31,639
I'm not helping you.

227
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:34,200
I'm helping Da Liang.

228
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,039
Oh, come on.

229
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,600
Da Yan and Da Liang are allies too.

230
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,440
This favor,

231
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,039
this princess will help!

232
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,200
Wonderful!

233
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,080
I knew you wouldn't be so disloyal.

234
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,200
Enjoy the food and drinks!

235
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:08,679
Greetings to the Crown Prince and envoys.

236
00:12:09,639 --> 00:12:11,200
Royal Uncle Liu is resting right now.

237
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,960
Why don't you return to your rooms

238
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:14,000
and come back later?

239
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:18,159
Why is he sleeping in broad daylight?

240
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:20,399
Seriously.

241
00:12:20,399 --> 00:12:22,279
Not even a welcome banquet?

242
00:12:22,559 --> 00:12:23,039
Ugh.

243
00:12:23,039 --> 00:12:23,440
Forget it.

244
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:24,600
If he sleeps, we sleep too.

245
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,279
We're tired anyway.

246
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:26,240
Let's sleep a couple hours and come back.

247
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,200
Farewell.

248
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:35,679
Steward.

249
00:12:37,039 --> 00:12:38,840
Greetings to the Crown Prince and envoys.

250
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,639
Well...

251
00:12:40,559 --> 00:12:42,039
Royal Uncle Liu hasn't woken up yet.

252
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,000
Hmm.

253
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:43,840
Still not awake?

254
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:44,639
Right.

255
00:12:44,879 --> 00:12:46,240
Then we'll sleep too.

256
00:13:47,799 --> 00:13:49,440
He really is just sleeping.

257
00:13:50,679 --> 00:13:51,240
Hey.

258
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:52,759
How about when the steward comes out,

259
00:13:52,759 --> 00:13:53,960
we grab him and ask?

260
00:13:54,639 --> 00:13:56,200
If there's something fishy going on,

261
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,960
what could you possibly get out of him?

262
00:14:01,039 --> 00:14:01,840
Hey.

263
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:03,840
He's coming out.

264
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:05,440
Hey!

265
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:05,840
Ouch!

266
00:14:06,159 --> 00:14:06,399
Ow!

267
00:14:06,399 --> 00:14:06,879
Stop hitting me!

268
00:14:07,279 --> 00:14:08,639
I'll talk!

269
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:09,879
Confess already!

270
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:11,759
Stop, stop hitting me!

271
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,519
I'll talk!

272
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,480
I'll talk!

273
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:15,879
Talk!

274
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:17,759
That wine,

275
00:14:17,879 --> 00:14:19,039
it's called Wandering Immortal Wine.

276
00:14:19,559 --> 00:14:20,639
A few months ago,

277
00:14:20,879 --> 00:14:21,159
the Prince

278
00:14:21,159 --> 00:14:23,039
bought it from a Western merchant.

279
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,039
They say drinking it gives vivid dreams.

280
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,360
Unless the wine's effect wears off,

281
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,200
or rather,

282
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:33,639
or unless

283
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:35,480
the bell on my belt is used,

284
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,200
he won't wake up.

285
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:43,320
Royal Uncle.

286
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,559
The Watanabe army has reached the border.

287
00:14:45,559 --> 00:14:46,200
We beg you...

288
00:15:10,799 --> 00:15:12,440
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

289
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,120
Wake up, wake up!

290
00:15:13,919 --> 00:15:14,720
What's going on?

291
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,440
Royal Uncle Liu woke up but didn't speak,

292
00:15:16,919 --> 00:15:17,720
drank the wine, and went back to sleep.

293
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,039
He's been addicted to dreams for months.

294
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,120
During these months,

295
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,679
aside from eating and using the toilet,

296
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:27,679
he spends all his time sleeping.

297
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:29,480
No matter who calls him,

298
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:30,720
he ignores them.

299
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:32,600
Why didn't you say so earlier?

300
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:34,480
You didn't give me a chance to!

301
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:35,720
So now,

302
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:36,759
is there any other way?

303
00:15:39,919 --> 00:15:40,399
Looks like

304
00:15:40,759 --> 00:15:41,240
we need to tackle this at the root.

305
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,759
We must find out why he loves dreaming,

306
00:15:45,399 --> 00:15:46,320
and what's in his dream

307
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:46,919
that fascinates him this much.

308
00:15:47,799 --> 00:15:48,279
How do we find out?

309
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:49,559
Don't tell me

310
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:50,399
we can go into his dream?

311
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,120
We can.

312
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:51,559
Mm.

313
00:15:54,159 --> 00:15:54,639
After drinking the Wandering Immortal Wine,

314
00:15:55,279 --> 00:15:56,679
people who sleep close together

315
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:58,840
will enter the same dream.

316
00:16:01,039 --> 00:16:01,240
Oh.

317
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:04,240
Got it.

318
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:09,440
Wait.

319
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,840
I have one more thing to say.

320
00:16:15,559 --> 00:16:16,879
Whoever falls asleep first,

321
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:19,320
that's whose dream you'll enter.

322
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,159
Make sure the Prince falls asleep first.

323
00:16:21,159 --> 00:16:21,559
Huh?

324
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,200
The Emperor's reward,

325
00:16:35,759 --> 00:16:37,399
you really don't want any of it?

326
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:41,240
Serving the Liang Kingdom

327
00:16:41,399 --> 00:16:42,720
is simply my duty.

328
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,159
Why would I need any reward?

329
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,200
But everyone in the palace is saying

330
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:50,000
that with all your battle achievements,

331
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:51,879
the Emperor intends

332
00:16:51,879 --> 00:16:54,320
to name you Crown Prince.

333
00:16:58,279 --> 00:16:59,600
Fighting wars is my forte.

334
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,799
But governing a kingdom,

335
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,279
let Fourth Brother handle that.

336
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:06,519
But...

337
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,119
Enough now.

338
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:07,759
Yue'er,

339
00:17:08,559 --> 00:17:09,559
focus on the chess game.

340
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,160
Mm.

341
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:13,920
Assassins!

342
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:14,720
Checkmate.

343
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,319
Easy, easy!

344
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:25,039
Oh ho!

345
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,720
So you're Liu Jun, huh?

346
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:27,839
Shut up!

347
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,599
How dare you address the Prince by name!

348
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:31,359
Oh.

349
00:17:32,519 --> 00:17:34,960
Quite handsome in his younger years, huh.

350
00:17:35,279 --> 00:17:36,839
Just back from fighting Watanabe.

351
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:40,720
Are you an assassin sent by Watanabe?

352
00:17:41,799 --> 00:17:42,240
No.

353
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,799
I mean, when you were young,

354
00:17:43,799 --> 00:17:45,039
you were so eager to fight Watanabe.

355
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,759
Why won't you help out now that you're old?

356
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,920
What nonsense!

357
00:17:52,359 --> 00:17:54,000
I am still young.

358
00:17:54,599 --> 00:17:55,880
How am I old?

359
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,240
Uh...

360
00:17:58,559 --> 00:17:59,319
Take him away.

361
00:17:59,319 --> 00:17:59,839
Lock him up.

362
00:18:00,279 --> 00:18:02,640
It's just a dream. Why would I fear you?

363
00:18:03,359 --> 00:18:04,160
Move!

364
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:16,960
You okay?

365
00:18:17,119 --> 00:18:17,920
I'm fine.

366
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,000
Let's go.

367
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:20,400
Hey!

368
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,400
Nobody's caught up, right?

369
00:18:31,599 --> 00:18:32,799
With my qinggong skills,

370
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,640
who could ever catch me?

371
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:38,799
This dream really seems quite real.

372
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,400
Hey.

373
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,200
The beatings feel pretty real too!

374
00:18:44,599 --> 00:18:45,400
Hey.

375
00:18:45,799 --> 00:18:46,599
Where's the Crown Prince?

376
00:18:47,279 --> 00:18:48,119
Don't worry about him.

377
00:18:48,119 --> 00:18:49,319
He can't die anyway.

378
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,200
Ah.

379
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,640
Besides, the palace is his home.

380
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:52,799
He can't get lost there.

381
00:18:53,319 --> 00:18:55,079
So what do we do now?

382
00:18:56,359 --> 00:18:57,400
Didn't we already say?

383
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,200
Wake Royal Uncle Liu from his dream.

384
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,400
How do we wake him up?

385
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,480
Didn't we agree already?

386
00:19:03,839 --> 00:19:05,480
Find the thing he's obsessed with,

387
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,519
then smash it to pieces.

388
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:07,319
That should do it.

389
00:19:07,519 --> 00:19:08,839
So based on this objective,

390
00:19:08,839 --> 00:19:10,839
I've drafted a detailed 18-step plan.

391
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:11,960
Step one...

392
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:12,720
Okay, okay.

393
00:19:13,119 --> 00:19:14,400
Your method is way too complicated.

394
00:19:14,559 --> 00:19:15,079
I have an idea.

395
00:19:15,319 --> 00:19:16,279
Follow me.

396
00:19:17,079 --> 00:19:17,880
Tsk.

397
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,240
Hey,

398
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,680
are you sure about this method?

399
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:28,839
Absolutely sure.

400
00:19:29,559 --> 00:19:31,079
Who cares what he's attached to?

401
00:19:31,119 --> 00:19:34,000
Just burn the whole palace down, done!

402
00:19:53,119 --> 00:19:54,440
This guy can really be

403
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,279
a hidden genius sometimes.

404
00:19:58,880 --> 00:19:59,680
Ha!

405
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,640
Watch the show!

406
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,240
Fire!

407
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,119
Fire!

408
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,720
Put it out, quick!

409
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,640
Fire!

410
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:09,000
Let's see you put this blaze out.

411
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:18,759
Huh?

412
00:20:20,119 --> 00:20:21,000
What's going on?

413
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:23,640
That works too?

414
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,000
Uh...

415
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:29,559
We're in Royal Uncle Liu's dream after all.

416
00:20:30,079 --> 00:20:31,640
He cherishes this place so much,

417
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,519
so even if something's slightly illogical,

418
00:20:33,519 --> 00:20:34,920
his subconscious will help him

419
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,640
protect it.

420
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:38,920
So what now?

421
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,039
No idea.

422
00:20:42,599 --> 00:20:44,519
Looks like we'll have to use the old way.

423
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,279
How is it?

424
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:03,200
Don't tell me it's braised pig trotters again.

425
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,119
Completely blank.

426
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,799
I can't sense anything.

427
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:10,720
Looks like your method fails in dreams.

428
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,000
This princess will have to handle it.

429
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:13,799
Hey, wait.

430
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,079
Let me step outside first.

431
00:21:15,079 --> 00:21:16,119
It's too gory.

432
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:17,599
Haha.

433
00:21:17,599 --> 00:21:18,599
Little brother.

434
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,400
Sorry about this.

435
00:21:20,519 --> 00:21:21,119
Ouyang Yan.

436
00:21:21,119 --> 00:21:22,400
Come quickly and look.

437
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,880
How did the weather change so suddenly?

438
00:21:29,119 --> 00:21:29,839
Let go of me!

439
00:21:29,839 --> 00:21:31,119
I'll beat you to death, I swear!

440
00:21:31,119 --> 00:21:31,880
Who are you?

441
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:32,720
How dare you tie me up!

442
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,240
You wretched woman!

443
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,680
What's going on?

444
00:21:39,559 --> 00:21:42,400
Wasn't she just terrified a moment ago?

445
00:21:43,079 --> 00:21:44,240
Royal Uncle Liu is angry.

446
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,079
Royal Uncle Liu must be furious right now.

447
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:47,160
Ah!

448
00:21:48,119 --> 00:21:48,920
That's why...

449
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,079
the weather has changed.

450
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,960
And people in the dream turn violent too.

451
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,279
Let's go find out first

452
00:21:54,519 --> 00:21:55,720
the reason he's angry.

453
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,880
It might just be the key to the dream.

454
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,799
Fourth Brother,

455
00:22:04,799 --> 00:22:06,640
Feelings are one thing,

456
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:08,079
the throne is another.

457
00:22:08,359 --> 00:22:09,599
These two matters,

458
00:22:09,599 --> 00:22:10,880
how can you lump them together?

459
00:22:11,319 --> 00:22:12,519
Hold your tongue right now.

460
00:22:12,519 --> 00:22:13,920
I'll pretend you said nothing.

461
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:14,720
Crown Prince.

462
00:22:15,079 --> 00:22:15,400
Shh.

463
00:22:16,079 --> 00:22:17,000
Why is he here?

464
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:19,000
I don't need your lectures.

465
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:21,759
Sixth Brother,

466
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:25,200
I don't believe you don't want the throne.

467
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,519
Oh.

468
00:22:27,119 --> 00:22:28,200
He's not the Crown Prince.

469
00:22:28,279 --> 00:22:29,799
He's the late Emperor in his youth.

470
00:22:31,839 --> 00:22:32,640
All these years,

471
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,680
risking your life in countless campaigns,

472
00:22:35,519 --> 00:22:36,839
earning so many military honors,

473
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:38,799
wasn't it all to make Father believe

474
00:22:38,799 --> 00:22:41,400
that you're worthy of the throne,

475
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,640
that you can protect Da Liang?

476
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:46,119
Serving the nation is my duty.

477
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,839
As for who's named Crown Prince,

478
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,720
that's Father's decision.

479
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,880
But no matter what,

480
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,759
this has nothing to do with Yue'er.

481
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:57,839
See?

482
00:22:57,839 --> 00:22:59,880
You still want the throne.

483
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:03,839
But are you sure

484
00:23:05,119 --> 00:23:08,880
you can really beat me to it?

485
00:23:10,119 --> 00:23:10,920
Unless...

486
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:14,119
you give Yue'er up to me,

487
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:16,359
then I won't fight you for the throne.

488
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:17,359
Shut your mouth!

489
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:21,920
So in their youth, these brothers fought

490
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:25,079
over a woman and the throne like this.

491
00:23:26,279 --> 00:23:26,839
But...

492
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,319
This must be why Royal Uncle Liu

493
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,640
came to resent the late Emperor,

494
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:32,160
and then

495
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,440
came to hate all of Da Liang.

496
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,119
So now that Watanabe is invading,

497
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:40,319
he refuses to send troops to help.

498
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,519
No.

499
00:23:43,519 --> 00:23:45,079
I can't let them turn on each other.

500
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,480
No, no.

501
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:48,319
Yue'er...

502
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,160
What do you take Yue'er for?

503
00:23:52,599 --> 00:23:53,079
Oh, come on!

504
00:23:53,079 --> 00:23:54,519
Stop arguing!

505
00:23:56,359 --> 00:23:57,119
You're brothers.

506
00:23:57,119 --> 00:23:58,279
Brothers!

507
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,160
You can't turn enemies over a woman.

508
00:24:00,799 --> 00:24:01,680
Who are you? Who do you think you are?

509
00:24:02,799 --> 00:24:04,160
Listen to me.

510
00:24:04,319 --> 00:24:05,759
After he dies,

511
00:24:05,839 --> 00:24:07,000
and you grow old,

512
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,000
Watanabe will invade Da Liang.

513
00:24:09,359 --> 00:24:10,200
And you,

514
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:10,880
Royal Uncle Liu,

515
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,920
because of this quarrel today,

516
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,079
will hold a grudge,

517
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:16,640
and refuse to send troops to help,

518
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:17,839
causing all of Da Liang

519
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,720
to fall into ruin.

520
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:20,680
What do you mean?

521
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,480
What nonsense are you spouting?

522
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,240
I'm not making this up.

523
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:25,359
He can vouch for me.

524
00:24:28,799 --> 00:24:29,680
Ouyang Yan,

525
00:24:30,319 --> 00:24:33,559
your stupidity is truly breathtaking.

526
00:24:36,599 --> 00:24:37,000
Aw, come on.

527
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,839
It's all just a dream anyway.

528
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:41,319
Don't take it to heart.

529
00:24:42,759 --> 00:24:44,000
How could Yan produce such a dumb princess?

530
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,240
My father and mother both say

531
00:24:50,759 --> 00:24:51,960
I'm smarter than the two of them!

532
00:24:52,799 --> 00:24:53,880
Now I see why Yan is in such decline.

533
00:24:56,359 --> 00:24:58,240
Don't you dare badmouth Yan!

534
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,000
So tell me,

535
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:08,519
What do we do now?

536
00:25:08,519 --> 00:25:09,400
Wait around to die.

537
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,960
Hey, don't be so negative.

538
00:25:12,359 --> 00:25:12,960
Fine, fine, fine.

539
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,839
In this dream, I owe you an apology.

540
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,000
Once we get out,

541
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,000
in the next dream,

542
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,240
I'll find you ten Hua Huas.

543
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:18,680
Hey.

544
00:25:19,519 --> 00:25:20,400
I won't mention Yan Kingdom,

545
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:21,559
and you don't mention Hua Hua.

546
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:24,000
Right.

547
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,599
Good point.

548
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,880
Let's go die.

549
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,240
You go by yourself.

550
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:30,160
Have a nice trip.

551
00:25:30,599 --> 00:25:31,559
No, wait.

552
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,000
I mean,

553
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,519
if we die in here,

554
00:25:35,519 --> 00:25:36,039
maybe

555
00:25:36,039 --> 00:25:38,240
we'll wake up in reality.

556
00:25:38,599 --> 00:25:40,599
I used to have dreams as a kid,

557
00:25:40,839 --> 00:25:42,200
and whenever I died in the dream,

558
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,559
I'd definitely wake up.

559
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,079
That's right!

560
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,720
Stab me with a blade.

561
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:50,359
But my

562
00:25:50,359 --> 00:25:53,400
blade was taken when I was locked up.

563
00:25:55,839 --> 00:25:56,200
But

564
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,319
we can ram into the wall!

565
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:04,880
Hmm.

566
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:06,880
This wall...

567
00:26:08,759 --> 00:26:10,000
isn't it a bit...

568
00:26:10,839 --> 00:26:13,160
Look, either you stay locked up here,

569
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:15,519
or you grit your teeth, steel yourself,

570
00:26:15,519 --> 00:26:16,480
and ram it!

571
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,119
You decide.

572
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,480
Of course I want to get out,

573
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,799
but the problem is this is a bit too...

574
00:26:23,079 --> 00:26:24,079
Too hard to commit to, right?

575
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:25,480
No worries.

576
00:26:25,839 --> 00:26:26,440
I'll help you.

577
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:46,200
Ouyang Yan,

578
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:51,000
I beg you, stay away from me!

579
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:54,480
After we get out of this dream,

580
00:26:55,319 --> 00:27:00,960
I'm retiring to the countryside.

581
00:27:01,079 --> 00:27:02,359
Homeward I go!

582
00:27:03,359 --> 00:27:07,640
My fields lie fallow, why not return?

583
00:27:10,079 --> 00:27:11,680
Hey, don't be like that.

584
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,519
We're in this together right now.

585
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:15,799
Can't turn on each other.

586
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:20,079
I suddenly miss Liu Heng so much.

587
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:21,519
Huh?

588
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:24,000
Why would you miss Liu Heng?

589
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,319
This way, please.

590
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:42,559
These two,

591
00:27:43,079 --> 00:27:44,440
I'll take them.
